  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>【What will you be working on】</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for sales activities such as creating new business opportunities and maintain current business and clients in ASEAN, India and Oceania region</li><li>Maintain good relationships and taking care of existing customers (Delivery, Costing, Coordination in quality issue)</li><li>Management of team member (Sales, Customer Service and Warehouse section)</li><li>Planning, Forecasting, and Preparing Sales budget in monthly and yearly</li><li>Coordinating and reporting regularly to Headquarters in Japan, and overseas factories</li></ul><p><strong>【 What they are looking for 】</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Bachelor's Degree</li><li>At least 15 years of sales experience in the Connector industry and 10 years of management experience (Automotive market preferable)</li><li>Proficient in Japanese (JLPT N1 equivalent) is a mandatory in order to liaise with native Japanese-speaking clients and Japan HQ</li><li>Familiar with automotive market, logistics, and import/export operations</li><li>Proficient in the latest Microsoft Excel & PowerPoint</li><li>Proven sales track record, and possesses strong communication and negotiation skills</li></ul><p>==========================</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>Registration No.: R1324853 (Misato Ogura)</p><p>Recruitment License : 12C5051</p>",
